	(11,10,2,'<p>Alfa bro is not only beautiful but completely functional, too. Almost every element of the equipment has some additional functions developed especially for the main festival of music and technologies ALFA FUTURE PEOPLE.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In the files of specification we hid several items to let the group participants make their guesses or suggest their own ideas.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To take part in the contest you should put your guesses in the comments to the notice in one of the AFP groups, and the jury (the festival organizers) will choose two winners &ndash; the one who will be the first to give the right answers and the one who will give the most creative answers. There also will be the Group choice award &ndash;for the most popular answer in the group.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The contest will take place till May 15. Every participant can give not more than five variants. The prizes for the first two places are the tickets to the festival! The group choice award is a branded souvenir.</p>\r\n<p>You can enter the competition on social networks Vkontakte, Facebook and Odnoklassniki) but keep in mind your can win only once.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://pp.vk.me/c617529/v617529234/aae4/aRlaPrirSgs.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"704\" height=\"420\" /></p>',1183),
	(12,13,2,'',136),
	(13,14,2,'<div class=\"block text border-in-admin\">\r\n<p>Matisse&amp; Sadko &ndash; these bright brothers-musicians, authors of the hits &laquo;Hi Scandinavia!&raquo;, &laquo;SLVR&raquo;, &laquo;Beatingof My Heart&raquo;, &laquo;Trio&raquo;, are among the most outstanding representatives of the Russian EDM.</p>\r\n<p>After their debut on Sensation2010, ArminvanBuuren invited brothers to release the track &laquo;Hi Scandinavia!&raquo; in his own label Armada. In the same year, Swedish House Mafia played this track in sets and radio-shows around the world. In 2012 Axwell, the frontman of SHM, expressed admiration for the works of Matisse &amp; Sadko from the stage of Record Grand Opening in Moscow. He called the Russian brothers house-mafia along with Swanky Tunes, Arty and Hard Rock Sofa. At the end of 2012 Swedish House Mafia inserted two compositions of Matisse &amp; Sadko in the farewell compilation &laquo;Until Now&raquo;.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>In 2013 Matisse &amp; Sadko together with Steve Angello created the composition &laquo;SLVR&raquo; which was the hundredth release of the lable SIZE. The track went to the top of the Beatport.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>Since 2013, Matisse &amp; Sadko have been working with Warner Music and last year brothers gave more than 100 performances worldwide.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Friends on Facebook: 121&nbsp;712</p>\r\n<p>Major hit: Hi Scandinavia!</p>\r\n<p>Views on YouTube: 78&nbsp;608&nbsp;<br /><br /></p>\r\n<div class=\"block socnet border-in-admin\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/MatisseSadko\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook</a> | <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/user/MatisseSadkoDJ\" target=\"_blank\">YouTube</a> | <a href=\"https://twitter.com/MatisseSadko\" target=\"_blank\">Twitter</a> | <a href=\"http://instagram.com/matissesadko\" target=\"_blank\">Instagram</a> | <a href=\"https://soundcloud.com/matisse_and_sadko\" target=\"_blank\">SoundCloud</a></div>\r\n</div>',136),
	(14,15,2,'',136),
	(15,13,2,'SWANKY TUNES',135),
	(16,14,2,'<div class=\"block text border-in-admin\">\r\n<p>Swanky Tunes band was founded in Smolensk in 1998 and immediately became a pioneer in many areas of Russian electronic music. For instance, Vadim Shpak, Dmitry Burykin and Stanislav Zaytsev - the founders and main and essential members of the group - are the first Russian musicians who recorded the track with such a heavyweight as Tiesto (\'MakeSomeNoise\', 2012).<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>Swanky Tunes are the first Russian DJs officially recognized in America and Europe. The trio fromSmolensk are also participants of the largest western festivals (Creamfileds (UK), Ultra Music Festival (Miami), Global Gathering (UK), Tomorrowland (Belgium)), and their music is released by the most famous and respected labels of the world - Musical Freedom (Tiesto) , Axtone (Axwell), Wall Recordings (Afrojack), Size (Steve Angello), Refune (Sebastian Ingrosso), Mixmash (Laidback Luke), Doorn Records (Sander van Doorn), Spinnin Records, Ultra, CR2, etc.</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<div class=\"block socnet border-in-admin\"><a href=\"http://www.swankytunes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">WebSite</a> | <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/swankytuneslive\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook</a> | <a href=\"http://vk.com/swankytunes\" target=\"_blank\">Vkontakte</a> | <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/user/swankytuneslive\" target=\"_blank\">YouTube</a> | <a href=\"http://twitter.com/swankytunes\" target=\"_blank\">Twitter</a> | <a href=\"http://instagram.com/swankytunes\" target=\"_blank\">Instagram</a> | <a href=\"http://soundcloud.com/swankytunes\" target=\"_blank\">SoundCloud</a></div>\r\n</div>',135),
