	(55,9,2,'<p>Dubstep producer and DJ Skrillex considers punk rock and the aesthetics of do-it-yourself to be his culture. He speaks about it in his exclusive interview to NME. He says that to create things he needs to control everything.&nbsp;</p>',1184),
	(56,10,2,'<p>Dubstep producer and DJ Skrillex considers punk rock and the aesthetics of do-it-yourself to be his culture. He speaks about it in his exclusive interview to NME. He says that to create things he needs to control everything.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>It has become known recently that the musician built the studio called \'The Nest\' in LA which can be used by electronic musicians. Speaking about it Skrillex says: \' We are some of few people who make decisions for the love of art, banal as it sounds.&nbsp; If you wish you can call it punk rock or DIY, it\'s my culture.</p>\r\n<p>Let us remind you that Skrillex released his debut album &laquo;Recess&raquo; in 2014 and will perform on the main stage of&nbsp; ALFA FUTURE PEOPLE on July 12 at 9pm.&nbsp;<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"/upload/content/2014Skrillex_NME_0605141.jpg\" alt=\"Photo: Zackery Michael/NME\" width=\"552\" height=\"368\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1184),
