	(59,3,2,'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1>How to get here<img class=\"bonus safit left\" src=\"/templates/_default_/images/safit.png\" alt=\"\" /><img class=\"bonus safit right\" src=\"/templates/_default_/images/safit.png\" alt=\"\" /></h1>\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">Coordinates GPS 56&deg;24\'58.6\"N 43&deg;44\'26.8\"E</h4>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class=\"block-text\">\r\n<div class=\"block-expand expanded\">\r\n<h3>FROM NIZHNIY NOVGOROD</h3>\r\n<div class=\"container\">\r\n<h4>Location map</h4>\r\n<a title=\"\" href=\"http://maps.yandex.ru/-/CVfXaAp2\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"scale\" src=\"/upload/content/nn.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></a><br />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>By train</h4>\r\nYou can reach the railway station Kozino by train from Nizhny Novgorod. Find the train-schedule on Russian Railways website, where you can also buy tickets: <a href=\"http://pass.rzd.ru/timetable/public/ru?STRUCTURE_ID=735&amp;layer_id=5354&amp;refererVpId=1&amp;refererPageId=704&amp;refererLayerId=4065#dir=0|tfl=3|checkSeats=0|withoutSeats=y|st0=%D0%9D%D0%98%D0%96%D0%9D%D0%98%D0%99%20%D0%9D%D0%9E%D0%92%D0%93%D0%9E%D0%A0%D0%9E%D0%94%7Ccode0=2060001|dt0=11.07.2014|st1=%D0%9A%D0%9E%D0%97%D0%98%D0%9D%D0%9E%7Ccode1=2061460|dt1=12.04.2014\">RZD.RU</a>.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<img class=\"close\" title=\"Закрыть\" src=\"/templates/_default_/images/tabs.info.close.png\" alt=\"Закрыть\" border=\"0\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"block-expand\">\r\n<h3>FROM KAZAN</h3>\r\n<div class=\"container\">\r\n<h4>Location map</h4>\r\n<a title=\"\" href=\"http://maps.yandex.ru/-/CVfXmD6v\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"scale\" src=\"/upload/content/kaz.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></a><br />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>By car</h4>\r\nTo get to the festival, you need to go along the Gorky Highway towards Moscow up to the route E22/Volga/M7. Drive along the highway M7, after you pass Nizhny Novgorod turn right at the direction sign towards Zavolzhie. Then go straight on till the T-junction, where you should turn right and keep going straight ahead until the turn to Bolshoe Kozino.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\nNow follow the signs and you will find the way directly to the festival!<br /><br />\r\n<p>If, for some reason, you haven&rsquo;t bought tickets to the site-parking of the festival, but you have a ticket of &ldquo;Standart&rdquo; category, than you can leave your car at guarded paid parking &ldquo;Autograd \", located on highway M7. Parking fee per day is 100 rubles.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>By train</h4>\r\nThere are direct and passing trains to Nizhny Novgorod from the railway station Kazan-Passajirskaya. Taking one of them you&rsquo;ll come to Moscow railway station, where you need to get the bus № 95, 57, 10, Т20, Т72,Т76 or shuttle № 76, №20. Get off at the stop for \"Dubravnaya street\" you will then have to wave down a taxi to get to the village Bolshoe Kozino.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\nMore information about the route and fare for special festival buses will appear shortly. Follow the updates!\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>By bus</h4>\r\nBuses depart from the central bus station of Kazan, which pass through Nizhny Novgorod, where they stop at the central bus station. There you have to take the bus №26 or №43 and get off at the Moscow railway station, where you then take the bus or a shuttle №95, which takes you to the stop \"Dubravnaya street\". Than you can wave down a taxi to get to the village Bolshoe Kozino or take specialized buses that run directly to the festival area.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\nMore information about the route and fare on special festival buses will appear shortly. Follow the updates!\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<img class=\"close\" title=\"Закрыть\" src=\"/templates/_default_/images/tabs.info.close.png\" alt=\"Закрыть\" border=\"0\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"block-expand\">\r\n<h3>FROM MOSCOW</h3>\r\n<div class=\"container\">\r\n<h4>Location map</h4>\r\n<a title=\"\" href=\"http://maps.yandex.ru/-/CVfX4W7-\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"scale\" src=\"/upload/content/msk24.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></a><br />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>By plane</h4>\r\n\"Aeroflot\", \"UTair\", \"Ural Airlines\" and some other airlines arrange flights from Moscow to Nizhny Novgorod. Timetable is available here: <a href=\"http://a.search.aviasales.ru/MOW1107GOJ1\">AVIASALES.RU</a>.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>By train</h4>\r\nNizhny Novgorod is reachable from Moscow by train. Look through the train-schedule on Russian Railways website, where you can also buy tickets: <a href=\"http://pass.rzd.ru/timetable/public/ru?STRUCTURE_ID=735&amp;layer_id=5354&amp;refererVpId=1&amp;refererPageId=704&amp;refererLayerId=4065#dir=0|tfl=3|checkSeats=0|withoutSeats=y|st0=%D0%9C%D0%9E%D0%A1%D0%9A%D0%92%D0%90%7Ccode0=2000000|dt0=11.07.2014|st1=%D0%9D%D0%B8%D0%B6%D0%BD%D0%B8%D0%B9%20%D0%9D%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B3%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B4%7Ccode1=2060001|dt1=12.04.2014\">RZD.RU</a>.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\nDuring the festival there will be specialized buses, which will shuttle from Moscow railway station in Nizhny Novgorod (Sq. Revolution, 2a) up to the concert stage.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\nIf you are a resident from Moscow (or you go through Moscow), you can go by high-speed train &ldquo;Sapsan&rdquo;, &ldquo;Lastochka&rdquo; or &ldquo;Burevestnik&rdquo;. All of them leave from Kursky railway station. You need to buy a ticket for &ldquo;Dzerzhinsk&rdquo; (direct to ATP) or Nizhny Novgorod (if you&rsquo;re going to stay in a hotel in the city). The train journey is around 4 hours.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>By car</h4>\r\nTo get to the festival, you need to drive along the M7 highway, pass the turning to Dzerzhinsk (to the right) and turn from the highway at the direction sign for Zavolzhie. Than go straight ahead to the T-junction, where you should turn right and keep on going straight ahead until the turn to Bolshoe Kozino.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\nIf you have a parking ticket or VIP- ticket, take the signs to the security parking area.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If, for some reason, you haven&rsquo;t bought tickets to the site-parking of the festival, but you have a ticket of &ldquo;Standart&rdquo; category, than you can leave your car at guarded paid parking &ldquo;Autograd \", located on highway M7. Parking fee per day is 100 rubles.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<img class=\"close\" title=\"Закрыть\" src=\"/templates/_default_/images/tabs.info.close.png\" alt=\"Закрыть\" border=\"0\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"block-expand\">\r\n<h3>FROM SAMARA</h3>\r\n<div class=\"container\">\r\n<h4>Location map</h4>\r\n<a title=\"\" href=\"http://maps.yandex.ru/-/CVfXmL2H\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"scale\" src=\"/upload/content/samara1.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></a><br />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>By train</h4>\r\nUnfortunately, there are no trains available on the route from Samara - Nizhniy Novgorod.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>By car</h4>\r\nTo get to the festival, you need to go along the M7 highway towards Moscow. After you pass Nizhniy Novgorod, turn off the highway at the direction sign for Zavolzhie (to the right). Then go straight ahead to the T-junction, where you should turn right and keep going straight ahead until the turning for Bolshoe Kozino.<br />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\nIf you have a parking ticket or VIP- ticket, take the signs to the security parking area.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If, for some reason, you haven&rsquo;t bought tickets to the site-parking of the festival, but you have a ticket of &ldquo;Standart&rdquo; category, than you can leave your car at guarded paid parking &ldquo;Autograd \", located on highway M7. Parking fee per day is 100 rubles.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<img class=\"close\" title=\"Закрыть\" src=\"/templates/_default_/images/tabs.info.close.png\" alt=\"Закрыть\" border=\"0\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"block-expand\">\r\n<h3>FROM ST. PETERSBURG</h3>\r\n<div class=\"container\">\r\n<h4>Location map</h4>\r\n<a title=\"\" href=\"http://maps.yandex.ru/-/CVfXm08Q\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"scale\" src=\"/upload/content/spb.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></a><br />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>By plane</h4>\r\n\"Aeroflot\", \"Russia airlines\" and some other airlines arrange flights from Moscow to Nizhny Novgorod. Timetable is available here: <a href=\"http://a.search.aviasales.ru/LED1107GOJ1\">AVIASALES.RU</a>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>By train</h4>\r\nNizhny Novgorod is reachable from St. Petersburg by train. Look through the train-schedule on Russian Railways website, where you can also buy tickets: <a href=\"http://pass.rzd.ru/timetable/public/ru?STRUCTURE_ID=735&amp;layer_id=5354&amp;refererVpId=1&amp;refererPageId=704&amp;refererLayerId=4065#dir=0|tfl=3|checkSeats=0|withoutSeats=y|st0=%D0%A1%D0%90%D0%9D%D0%9A%D0%A2-%D0%9F%D0%95%D0%A2%D0%95%D0%A0%D0%91%D0%A3%D0%A0%D0%93%7Ccode0=2004000|dt0=11.07.2014|st1=%D0%9D%D0%98%D0%96%D0%9D%D0%98%D0%99%20%D0%9D%D0%9E%D0%92%D0%93%D0%9E%D0%A0%D0%9E%D0%94%7Ccode1=2060001|dt1=12.04.2014\">RZD.RU</a>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\nIf you are coming to festival from Moscow (or you go through Moscow), you can go by high-speed train &ldquo;Sapsan&rdquo;, &ldquo;Lastochka&rdquo; or :Burevestnik&rdquo;. All of them leave from Kursky railway station. You need to buy a ticket for &ldquo;Dzerzhinsk&rdquo; (direct to ATP) or Nizhny Novgorod (if you&rsquo;re going to stay in a hotel in the city). The train journey is around 4 hours.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>By car</h4>\r\nYou need to take the M10 highway to Moscow, then head for the Ring Road-North towards Dmitrovskoe highway. After 19 km drive down to the highway and keep driving along the M7(Nizhny Novgorod).\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\nAfter you pass by the turn to Dzerzhinsk (to the right), turn off the highway at the direction sign for Zavolzhie (to the left). Then go straight ahead to the T-junction, where you should turn right and keep going straight ahead until the turning for Bolshoe Kozino.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\nIf you have a parking ticket or VIP- ticket, take the signs to the security parking area.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If, for some reason, you haven&rsquo;t bought tickets to the site-parking of the festival, but you have a ticket of &ldquo;Standart&rdquo; category, than you can leave your car at guarded paid parking &ldquo;Autograd \", located on highway M7. Parking fee per day is 100 rubles.</p>\r\n<br /><img class=\"close\" title=\"Закрыть\" src=\"/templates/_default_/images/tabs.info.close.png\" alt=\"Закрыть\" border=\"0\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"block-expand\">\r\n<h3>FROM SARANSK</h3>\r\n<div class=\"container\">\r\n<h4>Location map</h4>\r\n<a title=\"\" href=\"http://maps.yandex.ru/-/CVfXmT1y\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"scale\" src=\"/upload/content/saransk.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></a><br />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>By train</h4>\r\nNizhny Novgorod is reachable from Saransk by train. Look through the train-schedule on Russian Railways website, where you can also buy tickets: <a href=\"http://pass.rzd.ru/timetable/public/ru?STRUCTURE_ID=735&amp;layer_id=5354&amp;refererVpId=1&amp;refererPageId=704&amp;refererLayerId=4065#dir=0|tfl=3|checkSeats=0|withoutSeats=y|st0=%D0%A1%D0%90%D0%A0%D0%90%D0%9D%D0%A1%D0%9A%7Ccode0=2024700|dt0=11.07.2014|st1=%D0%9D%D0%98%D0%96%D0%9D%D0%98%D0%99%20%D0%9D%D0%9E%D0%92%D0%93%D0%9E%D0%A0%D0%9E%D0%94%7Ccode1=2060001|dt1=12.04.2014\">RZD.RU</a>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>By car</h4>\r\nTo get to the festival you need to drive along the road P158 towards Nizhny Novgorod, then drive down to the M7 highway. After you pass Nizhniy Novgorod, turn off the highway at the direction sign for Zavolzhie (to the right). Then go straight ahead to the T-junction, where you should turn right and keep going straight until the turning for Bolshoe Kozino.<br />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\nIf you have a parking ticket or VIP- ticket, take the signs to the security parking area.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If, for some reason, you haven&rsquo;t bought tickets to the site-parking of the festival, but you have a ticket of &ldquo;Standart&rdquo; category, than you can leave your car at guarded paid parking &ldquo;Autograd \", located on highway M7. Parking fee per day is 100 rubles.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<img class=\"close\" title=\"Закрыть\" src=\"/templates/_default_/images/tabs.info.close.png\" alt=\"Закрыть\" border=\"0\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"block-expand\">\r\n<h3>FROM CHEBOKSARY</h3>\r\n<div class=\"container\">\r\n<h4>Location map</h4>\r\n<a title=\"\" href=\"http://maps.yandex.ru/-/CVfXmX8P\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"scale\" src=\"/upload/content/cheb.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></a><br />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>By train</h3>\r\nUnfortunately, there are no trains available on the route from Cheboksary - Nizhniy Novgorod.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>By car</h3>\r\nTo get to the festival you need to drive along Octyabrskaya road towards the Volga/M7 highway and Moscow. After you pass Nizhniy Novgorod, turn off the highway at the direction sign Zavolzhie (to the right). Then go straight ahead to the T-junction, where you should turn to the right and keep going straight until the turning to Bolshoe Kozino.<br />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\nIf you have a parking ticket or VIP- ticket, take the signs to the security parking area.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If, for some reason, you haven&rsquo;t bought tickets to the site-parking of the festival, but you have a ticket of &ldquo;Standart&rdquo; category, than you can leave your car at guarded paid parking &ldquo;Autograd \", located on highway M7. Parking fee per day is 100 rubles.</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<img class=\"close\" title=\"Закрыть\" src=\"/templates/_default_/images/tabs.info.close.png\" alt=\"Закрыть\" border=\"0\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>',7),
