	(180,10,2,'<p><strong></strong>Great news for lovers of quality &laquo;niche electronics&raquo;! Line-up of ALFA FUTURE PEOPLE replenished with two participants: DJ Carnage and Dusky.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>DJ Carnage, dweller of sunny Los Angeles, became famous for incendiary mixes of electronics, pop and hip-hop. Moreover, an inexhaustible drive and catchy melodies of Carnage were appreciated not only by clubbers, but also by his brother in arms - DJ! His tracks are regularly heard on the Tiesto podcast and radio show &laquo;Planet Perfecto&raquo; by Paul Oakenfold. Uncompromising electro-dubstep track &laquo;Bang&raquo; is a Carnage&rsquo;s essential composition.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><iframe style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/lwMc_W9K-J8?rel=0\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>British electronic duo Dusky was formed in 2009. Just in 3 years the team has managed to release a number of successful releases and enlist the support of respected labels and artists. Dusky style developes from organic combination of classic Detroit techno and UK dance garage.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>April 2014 Dusky got on the cover of the legendary magazine DJ Mag, and before long they will release their new album &laquo;Love Takin Over&raquo; on their own label.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In waiting for the album and the duo set at AFP, let&rsquo;s watch the story of one day of a girl - video &laquo;No More&raquo;.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><iframe style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/a76cZzp0mIE?rel=0\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>',1191),
