	(189,10,2,'<p>To get to the festival you can take high-speed train &ldquo;Sapsan&rdquo;, &ldquo;Lastochka&rdquo; or &ldquo;Burevestnik&rdquo;. All of them leave from Kursky railway station. Tickets to &ldquo;Nizhny Novgorod&rdquo; for July 11 will be available for purchase from Mai 28<sup>th</sup>. The train arrives to Moscow Railway station in Nizhny Novgorod (Sq. Revolution, 2a), from where branded shuttles leave. Roundtrip transportation between Sq. Revolution, 2a and Festival AFP will be carried out during the festival.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We suggest you to buy tickets in advance, because the number of tickets is limited. Do not miss the main music event of this summer!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Look through the train-schedule on Russian Railways website, where you can also buy tickets:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://pass.rzd.ru/timetable/public/ru?STRUCTURE_ID=735&amp;layer_id=5354&amp;refererVpId=1&amp;refererPageId=704&amp;refererLayerId=4065#dir=0|tfl=3|checkSeats=0|withoutSeats=y|st0=%D0%9C%D0%9E%D0%A1%D0%9A%D0%92%D0%90%7Ccode0=2000000|dt0=11.07.2014|st1=%D0%9D%D0%B8%D0%B6%D0%BD%D0%B8%D0%B9%20%D0%9D%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B3%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B4%7Ccode1=2060001|dt1=12.04.2014\">RZD.RU</a>.</p>',1192),
